/
  Type-registry render vectors — v1 (DERIVED drift/diff target)
  Source:  entity-core-go types.RegisterCoreTypes + connect/tree handler
           types (== validate-peer runTypeSystem registry).
  Status:  NOT an arch-authored canonical corpus (S5). Regenerate from
           the Go oracle when entity-core-go moves. The sibling
           `type-registry-vectors-v1.cbor` is the canonical-ECF build
           artifact (array of {name, tree_path, content_hash, data}).
  Use:     a peer renders its own system/type/<name> entities natively
           and diffs each content_hash against this set (S8 golden-file).
  Format:  CBOR diagnostic notation, RFC 8949 §8. `data` is the
           ECF-encoded TypeDefinition payload (entity data).
  Count:   150 types.
/

